      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CAPE COD (6) started even-money and did a good job but found one better on debut last time out over 900m at Newcastle. Beautifully bred filly who will appreciate a bit more ground today. Clearly the one to beat but the price on offer will be prohibitive. FLAUNTER (10) worked home well to get up for second in an impressive debut over 1000m at this track recently. Tricky gate diluted by scratchings. Will be hard to hold out over a bit more ground today in a small field. NORTHERN EAGLE (2) found the line well at Tamworth on Friday, beaten only 0.3 lengths over 1400m. The quick back-up is a positive message from the stable. Impossible to make a case for the other runners - KRYSTINA KERIMA (8) is probably the pick of them for first four players following a slightly better effort at Muswellbrook last start.",
